<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3450474>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Clathria (Axosuberites) hillenburgi n. sp. (UFPEPOR 1975). A, choanosomal principal styles (I); B, choanosomal principal styles (II); C, subectosomal subtylostyles; D, styles I detail; E, subtylostyles detail; F, styles II detail; G, palmate isochelae; H, toxas. Scale bars: A, C = 100 μm; B, D–F, H = 50 μm; G = 20 μm." ;
